726650f-a.title: Queens: Union Turnpike - Grand Central Parkway
726650f-a.text:
Flushing Meadow Park (Cueens): Two views of the expansive
grounds of the New York World's Fair 1939-40, viewing north from
nior Turnpike at Grand Central Parkway. The body of water is
Willow -aake, in the amusement area, and across it is the main ex-
position center with the perisphere and Trylon--the Fair's theme--
clearly visible; to its ri:ht is the parachute jump. On the left,
running parallel to the park, is Grand Central Tarkway.
May 30, 1939
Views 1,2
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODICTIONS
